abstract: Indian Prime Minister Narendra Modi's party lost control of another state on Monday, adding to a string of electoral losses since last December amid protests that mark the biggest challenge to the Hindu-nationalist leader.
snippet: Indian Prime Minister Narendra Modi's party lost control of another state on Monday, adding to a string of electoral losses since last December amid protests that mark the biggest challenge to the Hindu-nationalist leader.
lead_paragraph: NEW DELHI — Indian Prime Minister Narendra Modi's party lost control of another state on Monday, adding to a string of electoral losses since last December amid protests that mark the biggest challenge to the Hindu-nationalist leader.
headline_main: Modi's Party Loses Indian State Election Amid Protests Over Citizenship Law
headline_print_headline: Modi's Party Loses Indian State Election Amid Protests Over Citizenship Law

abstract: Joe Biden’s presidential bid got a boost Monday from one of the leading Latinos in Congress, with the chairman of the Hispanic Caucus' political arm endorsing the former vice president as Democrats’ best hope to defeat President Donald Trump.
snippet: Joe Biden’s presidential bid got a boost Monday from one of the leading Latinos in Congress, with the chairman of the Hispanic Caucus' political arm endorsing the former vice president as Democrats’ best hope to defeat President Donald Trump.
lead_paragraph: Joe Biden’s presidential bid got a boost Monday from one of the leading Latinos in Congress, with the chairman of the Hispanic Caucus' political arm endorsing the former vice president as Democrats’ best hope to defeat President Donald Trump.
headline_main: Biden's New Endorsement Reflects Battle for Latino Support
headline_print_headline: Biden's New Endorsement Reflects Battle for Latino Support

abstract: About 200 opposition lawmakers and supporters protested in Sri Lanka's capital on Monday to condemn the arrest of a former Cabinet minister whose political defection in 2014 triggered the fall of the government led by the brother of the current president.
snippet: About 200 opposition lawmakers and supporters protested in Sri Lanka's capital on Monday to condemn the arrest of a former Cabinet minister whose political defection in 2014 triggered the fall of the government led by the brother of the current pr...
lead_paragraph: COLOMBO, Sri Lanka — About 200 opposition lawmakers and supporters protested in Sri Lanka's capital on Monday to condemn the arrest of a former Cabinet minister whose political defection in 2014 triggered the fall of the government led by the brother of the current president.
headline_main: Opposition Lawmakers Protest Arrest of Ex-Cabinet Minister
headline_print_headline: Opposition Lawmakers Protest Arrest of Ex-Cabinet Minister

abstract: Baba Ram Dass, the 1960s counterculture spiritual leader who experimented with LSD and traveled to India to find enlightenment, returning to share it with Americans, has died. He was 88.
snippet: Baba Ram Dass, the 1960s counterculture spiritual leader who experimented with LSD and traveled to India to find enlightenment, returning to share it with Americans, has died. He was 88.
lead_paragraph: MAUI, Hawaii — Baba Ram Dass, the 1960s counterculture spiritual leader who experimented with LSD and traveled to India to find enlightenment, returning to share it with Americans, has died. He was 88.
headline_main: Baba Ram Dass, Spiritual Guru and LSD Pioneer, Dies at 88
headline_print_headline: Baba Ram Dass, Spiritual Guru and LSD Pioneer, Dies at 88

abstract: Pro-government activists in Nigeria on Monday attacked civil society protesters who were demanding the release of people they say are illegally detained, a Reuters witness said.
snippet: Pro-government activists in Nigeria on Monday attacked civil society protesters who were demanding the release of people they say are illegally detained, a Reuters witness said.
lead_paragraph: ABUJA — Pro-government activists in Nigeria on Monday attacked civil society protesters who were demanding the release of people they say are illegally detained, a Reuters witness said.
headline_main: Pro-Government Group Attacks Rally Demanding Release of 'Illegally' Held Nigerians
headline_print_headline: Pro-Government Group Attacks Rally Demanding Release of 'Illegally' Held Nigerians

abstract: Boeing Co has fired Chief Executive Officer Dennis Muilenburg, following a year of intense scrutiny and industrial setbacks set off by twin fatal crashes of its 737 MAX jetliner.
snippet: Boeing Co has fired Chief Executive Officer Dennis Muilenburg, following a year of intense scrutiny and industrial setbacks set off by twin fatal crashes of its 737 MAX jetliner.
lead_paragraph: (Reuters) - Boeing Co has fired Chief Executive Officer Dennis Muilenburg, following a year of intense scrutiny and industrial setbacks set off by twin fatal crashes of its 737 MAX jetliner.
headline_main: Boeing Fires CEO Muilenburg as 737 MAX Crisis Deepens
headline_print_headline: Boeing Fires CEO Muilenburg as 737 MAX Crisis Deepens

abstract: Today’s A1 is the result of a far more democratic and organic process than the one in place when I arrived at The Times in 1978.
snippet: Today’s A1 is the result of a far more democratic and organic process than the one in place when I arrived at The Times in 1978.

abstract: Iran began new operations on Monday at a heavy water nuclear reactor, the head of the country's nuclear agency said. The move was designed to intensify pressure on Europe to find an effective way around U.S. sanctions that block Tehran’s oil sales abroad.

lead_paragraph: TEHRAN, Iran — Iran began new operations on Monday at a heavy water nuclear reactor, the head of the country's nuclear agency said. The move was designed to intensify pressure on Europe to find an effective way around U.S. sanctions that block Tehran’s oil sales abroad.
headline_main: Iran Starts New Operations at Heavy Water Reactor
